I know that the particle will move in the direction of the gradient, hence I calculated the gradient$$\vec{
abla}f(x,y)=(2xy^2,2x^2y)\underbrace{\Rightarrow}_{x=1,y=2}\vec{
abla}f=(8,4)$$
Now, I think that the particle will stop when it reaches the origin, but I'm not sure it is true, and if it is true how to explain it. Also, I don't understand how the calculation of $\vec{
abla}f(x,y)$ could help me in finding the explicit form of the path. Please help, thank you.
